{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id05d30706-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s2395"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2395"},"text":"§ 2395.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Judicial review","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id05d30707-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s2395/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Petition for review; time and place of filing","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A worker, group of workers, certified or recognized union, or authorized representative of such worker or group aggrieved by a final determination of the Secretary of Labor under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t19/s2273"},"text":"section 2273 of this title","children":[],"tail":", a firm or its representative or any other interested domestic party aggrieved by a final determination of the Secretary of Commerce under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t19/s2341"},"text":"section 2341 of this title","children":[],"tail":", an agricultural commodity producer (as defined in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t19/s2401/2"},"text":"section 2401(2) of this title","children":[],"tail":") aggrieved by a determination of the Secretary of Agriculture under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t19/s2401b"},"text":"section 2401b of this title","children":[],"tail":", or a community or any other interested domestic party aggrieved by a final determination of the Secretary of Commerce under section 2371 "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002110"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002110"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" See References in Text note below."}],"tail":" of this title may, within sixty days after notice of such determination, commence a civil action in the United States Court of International Trade for review of such determination. The clerk of such court shall send a copy of the summons and the complaint in such action to the Secretary of Labor, the Secretary of Commerce, or the Secretary of Agriculture, as the case may be. Upon receiving a copy of such summons and complaint, such Secretary shall promptly certify and file in such court the record on which he based such determination."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id05d30708-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s2395/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Findings of fact by Secretary; conclusiveness; new or modified findings","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The findings of fact by the Secretary of Labor, the Secretary of Commerce, or the Secretary of Agriculture, as the case may be, if supported by substantial evidence, shall be conclusive; but the court, for good cause shown, may remand the case to such Secretary to take further evidence, and such Secretary may thereupon make new or modified findings of fact and may modify his previous action, and shall certify to the court the record of the further proceedings. Such new or modified findings of fact shall likewise be conclusive if supported by substantial evidence.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id05d30709-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s2395/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Determination; review by Supreme Court","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Court of International Trade shall have jurisdiction to affirm the action of the Secretary of Labor, the Secretary of Commerce, or the Secretary of Agriculture, as the case may be, or to set such action aside, in whole or in part. The judgment of the Court of International Trade shall be subject to review by the United States Court of Appeals for the Federal Circuit as prescribed by the rules of such court. The judgment of the Court of Appeals for the Federal Circuit shall be subject to review by the Supreme Court of the United States upon certiorari as provided in section 1256 ","children":[{"tag":"sup","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" of title 28."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id05d3070a-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/618/tII/s284"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–618, title II, § 284","children":[],"tail":", as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/417/tVI/s613/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–417, title VI, § 613(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-10-10"},"text":"Oct. 10, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/1746"},"text":"94 Stat. 1746","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/164/tI/s163/a/5"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–164, title I, § 163(a)(5)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-04-02"},"text":"Apr. 2, 1982","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/49"},"text":"96 Stat. 49","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/182/tV/s503/d"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–182, title V, § 503(d)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1993-12-08"},"text":"Dec. 8, 1993","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/107/2151"},"text":"107 Stat. 2151","children":[],"tail":"; "}